#### Introduction
{:.pb-1}

Once you have __crafted__ your perfect view by [filtering]({% link _tutorials/view/easy_filtering.md %}) the data from sheets, you can then generate a __sharable__ link.

#### Process
{:.pt-2 .pb-1}

![Link Export Screenshot][1]{:class="img-fluid img-thumbnail mx-auto d-block"}

When you click on the __Create__ command (from the _Share_ menu), you will see a dialog similar to the one above. The __long link in the center__ is your sharable link. You can use the __Test Link__ button to do the following things:

+ __Test Link__ - Click on this button itself to open the view link in a new tab, so you can __test it before sharing__. If you need to make any changes, you can return to your view and adjust your filters and column visibilities.
+ __Copy__ - On the button drop-down menu, you can click here to copy the view link to your clipboard so that you can copy it straight into an email.
+ __Details__ - This will show you the __filter__ data encoded within the link. A view link is essentially a __set of instructions__, telling the app which sheet to open and what filter to apply to the data.
+ __Shorten__ - Using the [Google Links Shortener](https://goo.gl){:target="_blank"}, this will generate a shorter version of your link. This is easier to share (as the link itself is much shorter), and you can also track how many times it has been used!

If you would prefer to use a [QR Code](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/QR_code){:target="_blank" rel="noopener"}, instead of a regular link, then clicking the black button (on the right hand side) will reveal a QR code that can be quickly copied or displayed on a larger screen.

#### Finally
{:.pt-2 .pb-1}

Each link that you generate will be __unique to the filters__ that you set up __before creating it__. You can create as __many different filters__ (e.g. for different departments or subjects) for a single sheet as you would like. Each link will __work independently__ of all other ones.
